This paper focuses on the identification of Technical Debt in pull requests, which is a software engineering practice. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the different types of Technical Debt, which can be related to programming languages (cs.PL - Programming Languages) and code quality (cs.CE - Computer Engineering). The rejection of pull requests can also be related to security issues (cs.CR - Cryptography and Security) and software development practices (cs.SD - Software Development).
